daffy doodles is a warner bros. looney tunes cartoon featuring daffy duck and porky pig, produced in 1945, and released in 1946. daffy is the notorious "moustache fiend", bent on putting a mustache on every lip in sight, while porky is a police officer intent on capturing daffy. this cartoon is the first full-length cartoon that animator robert mckimson directed. mel blanc provided the voices for the characters, and warren foster was the writer.